Installation
============

This package is built inside a MicroBooNE ubana MRB area on the GPVM.
The steps below match the setup that worked on uboonegpvm05.


1. Start from the GPVM and enter the container
----------------------------------------------

    ssh <your-fnal-username>@uboonegpvm05.fnal.gov
    cd /exp/uboone/app/users/$USER/production
    /cvmfs/uboone.opensciencegrid.org/bin/shell_apptainer.sh
    source /cvmfs/uboone.opensciencegrid.org/products/setup_uboone_mcc9.sh


2. Make a fresh MRB area
------------------------

Use a new empty directory. mrb newDev fails if the directory already has
content.

    mkdir mcc9
    cd mcc9
    mrb newDev -q e17:prof
    source localProducts_*/setup


3. Get ubana
------------

    mrb g ubana
    cd srcs/ubana
    git checkout tags/v08_00_00_92
    cd ubana


4. Clone this repository into ubana
-----------------------------------

    git clone https://github.com/njlane314/searchingforstrangeness.git
    cd searchingforstrangeness
    source .setup.sh


5. Add it to the ubana build
----------------------------

Edit:

    srcs/ubana/ubana/CMakeLists.txt

Make it look like this:

    #add_subdirectory(AnalysisTree)
    #add_subdirectory(Calibrations)
    #add_subdirectory(ChargedTrackMultiplicity)
    #add_subdirectory(CosmicTagging)
    #add_subdirectory(Filters)
    #add_subdirectory(HitAnalysis)
    #add_subdirectory(LEEPhotonAnalysis)
    #add_subdirectory(LLApp)
    #add_subdirectory(MicroBooNEWireCell)
    #add_subdirectory(OpticalDetectorAna)
    #add_subdirectory(PatternFilter)
    #add_subdirectory(TPCNeutrinoIDFilter)
    #add_subdirectory(UBXSec)
    #add_subdirectory(LArSoftExamples)
    #add_subdirectory(HSNAnalysis)
    #add_subdirectory(XGBoost)
    #add_subdirectory(NCElastic)
    #add_subdirectory(ParticleID)
    #add_subdirectory(SinglePhotonAnalysis)
    #add_subdirectory(TreeReader)
    #add_subdirectory(Arborist)
    #add_subdirectory(searchingfornues)
    add_subdirectory(searchingforstrangeness)
    add_subdirectory(redk2nu)

That is the minimal working ubana build used here: all the usual ubana
subdirectories are commented out, searchingfornues is disabled, and only
searchingforstrangeness plus redk2nu stay active.

If you want the source tree to match that minimal build exactly, you can also
remove the other directories under srcs/ubana/ubana and keep only:

    redk2nu
    searchingforstrangeness

That is what worked in the GPVM setup shown above.


6. Build
--------

From inside searchingforstrangeness:

    source .build.sh


Notes
-----

.setup.sh sets up the MCC9 environment, local products, and token.
.build.sh runs mrb i -j8 from $MRB_TOP.
After the build, use USAGE for runtime instructions.
